# Survey

-[[[Cai99-ECCC]]] J.-Y. Cai. Some recent progress on the complexity of lattice problems. (ECCC TR99-006)
-NTRU Cryptosystems. [[Peer Review and Independent Scrutiny of the NTRUEncrypt Public Key Cryptosystem:http://www.ntru.com/cryptolab/pdf/NTRU_Peer_Review_122001.pdf]] [pdf]
-O. Regev. &ldquo;Lattice-based cryptography&rdquo; (CRYPTO 2006)
-D. Micciancio and O. Regev. &ldquo;Lattice-based cryptography.&rdquo; (In Post-Quantum Cryptology)
-J. Buchmann, R. Lindner, M. R&uuml;ckert, and M. Schneider. &ldquo;Post-Quantum Cryptography: Lattice Signatures.&rdquo; (CECC 2008)
-C. Peikert. &ldquo;Some Recent Progress in Lattice-Based Cryptography .&rdquo; (TCC 2009) 
-- Slides are available at Peikert's web site
-D. Micciancio. &ldquo;The Geometry of Lattice Cryptography.&rdquo; (FOSAD VI, 2011)
-Xavier Boyen. &ldquo;Expressive Encryption Systems from Lattices.&rdquo; (CANS 2011)
-Thijs Laarhoven and Joop van de Pol and Benne de Weger. &ldquo;Solving Hard Lattice Problems and the Security of Lattice-Based Cryptosystems.&rdquo; ( [[Cryptology ePrint Archive - Report 2012/533:http://eprint.iacr.org/2012/533]] )
-[[[BCKSS12-Tatra]]] Rachid El Bansarkhani, Daniel Cabarcas, Po-Chun Kuo, Patrick Schmidt, Michael Schneider: A Selection of Recent Lattice-Based Signature and Encryption Schemes

